Package: castSDM
Type: Package
Title: Causal-Aware Species Distribution Modeling
Version: 0.3.0
Author: Liqiang Q [aut, cre, cph] (ORCID: <https://orcid.org/0009-0002-6966-4633>)
Maintainer: Liqiang Q <2759831686@qq.com>
Authors@R: c(
    person(
            "Liqiang", "Q",
      email = "2759831686@qq.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-6966-4633")
    )
  )
Description: Integrates causal DAG-guided variable selection with species
    distribution modeling. Learns species-specific causal structures via
    Directed Acyclic Graphs (DAG) using PC, two-stage MB-First (IAMB + local
    PC), or bootstrap Hill-Climbing algorithms, then selects ecologically
    relevant predictors through Markov Blanket extraction and RF importance
    screening. Fits an ensemble of standard SDM algorithms (Random Forest,
    BRT, MaxEnt, GAM) with performance-weighted ensemble prediction.
    Supports future climate projection via CMIP6 data and spatial
    cross-validation.
